### Access Drizzle ORM for Database Queries (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/sqlite.mdx

This TypeScript example demonstrates how to directly access Drizzle's querying and selection APIs via `payload.db.drizzle` after generating the schema. It shows importing a type-safe table definition and performing both `findMany()` queries and more complex `select()` operations with `where()` clauses, utilizing Drizzle's powerful expression builders.

```ts
// Import table from the generated file
import { posts } from './payload-generated-schema'
// To avoid installing Drizzle, you can import everything that drizzle has from our re-export path.
import { eq, sql, and } from '@payloadcms/db-sqlite/drizzle'

// Drizzle's Querying API: https://orm.drizzle.team/docs/rqb
const posts = await payload.db.drizzle.query.posts.findMany()
// Drizzle's Select API https://orm.drizzle.team/docs/select
const result = await payload.db.drizzle
  .select()
  .from(posts)
  .where(
    and(eq(posts.id, 50), sql`lower(${posts.title}) = 'example post title'`),
  )
```

